	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hehe. The staff of the wheel /can/ actually do some damage. I've gotten the killing blow on the Solusek Kobold King (42 SK) with it. And promptly danced around and made fun of the tanks in the group. Okay, so it isn't going to swing the balance of a fight. But it's amusing to do, and it does come in handy at times. Sure, you're not going to beat down that LDC singlehandedly with your mighty staff, but do you really want to spend a Conflag on one of those annoying undead that attack you even though you're 40 levels higher than them? (Skeletons. The definition of bonehead) I just whip out my weeping wand and have some fun.<br><br><br>Cryselle Silverwynd<br>Hell 45 wizardess<br>Tribunal<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
