	   <tr><td colspan=2>A lower level kiting technique is the circle of death grouping with a Druid. He sows both members, then he goes out and snares (and swarms) a yellow/red beast, comes back to you (running around you in a circle), you start casting the DD's until the mob turns on you... you then run around (in a circle) as the druid casts DD's until it turns back on the druid which means you cast DD's again, etc... works from L14 druids up<br>Say L12 to L16 wizards as a start, all the way up to 24<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
